<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2789/1999 of 22 December 1999 laying down the marketing standard for table grapes </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2789/1999, millega s&auml;testatakse lauaviinamarjade turustusstandard 22. detsember 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES. </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2200/96 of 28 October 1996 on the common organisation of the market in fruit and vegetables (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1257/1999 (2), and in particular Article 2(2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 28. oktoobri 1996. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2200/96 puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1257/1999, (2) eriti selle artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) table grapes are among the products listed in Annex I to Regulation (EC) No 2200/96 for which standards must be adopted. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) lauaviinamarjad on m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2200/96 I lisas toodete hulgas, mille standardid tuleb vastu v&otilde;tta. </eesti>
<inglise> Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1730/87 laying down quality standards for table grapes (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 888/97 (4), has been amended frequently and can no longer ensure legal clarity: </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1730/87, millega s&auml;testatakse lauaviinamarjade kvaliteedistandardid, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 888/97, (4) on korduvalt muudetud ning see ei ole enam juriidiliselt selge; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Regulation (EEC) No 1730/87 should be repealed and the rules it contains recast. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 1730/87 tuleks kehtetuks tunnistada ja seal sisalduvaid eeskirju uuendada. </eesti>
<inglise> To that end in the interest of preserving transparency on the world market, account should be taken of the standard for table grapes recommended by the Working Party on Standardisation of Perishable Produce and Quality Development of the United Nations Economic Commission for Europe (UN/ECE): </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks tuleks maailmaturu l&auml;bipaistvuse huvides arvesse v&otilde;tta lauaviinamarjade standardit, mida on soovitanud &Uuml;RO Euroopa Majanduskomisjoni riknevate toodete standardimise ja kvaliteedi arendamise t&ouml;&ouml;r&uuml;hm; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) applying this standard should result in products of unsatisfactory quality being removed from the market, bringing production into line with consumer requirements and facilitating trade relationships based on fair competition, thereby helping improve the profitability of production: </inglise>
<eesti> 3) selle standardi kohaldamine peaks ebarahuldava kvaliteediga tooted turult k&otilde;rvaldama, viima tootmise vastavusse tarbijate n&otilde;udmistega ja h&otilde;lbustama ausal konkurentsil p&otilde;hinevaid kaubandussuhteid, parandades seel&auml;bi tootmise tasuvust; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) the standard applies at all marketing stages. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) seda standardit kohaldatakse k&otilde;ikidel turustusetappidel. </eesti>
<inglise> Longdistance transport, storage over a certain period and the various processes which the products undergo may cause certain alterations owing to the biological development of the products or their relatively perishable nature. </inglise>
<eesti> Toodete pikamaavedu, teatav ladustusaeg v&otilde;i mitmesugused toodetega tehtavad toimingud v&otilde;ivad kaasa tuua nende bioloogilisest arengust v&otilde;i suuremast v&otilde;i v&auml;iksemast riknemisohust p&otilde;hjustatud kvaliteedi halvenemise. </eesti>
<inglise> Account should be taken of such deterioration when applying the standard at the marketing stages which follow dispatch. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda riknemist tuleks seet&otilde;ttu arvesse v&otilde;tta l&auml;hetamisj&auml;rgsetel turustusetappidel standardeid kohaldades. </eesti>
<inglise> Since products in the 'Extra' class must be sorted and packaged with particular care, only lack of freshness and turgidity is to be taken into account in their case: </inglise>
<eesti> Et ekstraklassi tooteid tuleb eriti hoolikalt sortida ja pakkida, v&otilde;ib nende puhul arvesse v&otilde;tta &uuml;ksnes v&auml;rskuse ja turdumuse v&auml;henemist; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) there is a developing demand for small packages containing table grapes of different origins or varieties. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) n&otilde;udlus erineva p&auml;ritoluga ja erinevaid viinamarjasorte sisaldavate v&auml;ikepakendite j&auml;rele on kasvanud. </eesti>
<inglise> This type of presentation should therefore be authorised for table grapes, and the provisions governing marking should be adjusted accordingly: </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu tuleks seda lauaviinamarjade esitusviisi lubada ning m&auml;rgistamisn&otilde;udeid vastavalt kohandada. </eesti>
<inglise> (6) the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Fresh Fruit and Vegetables, </inglise>
<eesti> 6) k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las v&auml;rske puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;givilja korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE: </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The marketing standard for table grapes falling within CN code 0806 10 10 shall be as set out in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> CN-koodi 0806 10 10 alla kuuluvate viinamarjade turustusstandard on s&auml;testatud lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> The standard shall apply at all stages of marketing under the conditions laid down in Regulation (EC) No 2200/96. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda standardit kohaldatakse k&otilde;ikidel turustusetappidel m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2200/96 s&auml;testatud tingimuste kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> However, at stages following dispatch, the products may show in relation to the requirements of the standard: </inglise>
<eesti> L&auml;hetamisj&auml;rgsetel etappidel v&otilde;ib toodetel siiski esineda vastupidiselt etten&auml;htud standarditele: </eesti>
<inglise> -a slight lack of freshness and turgidity, </inglise>
<eesti> - v&auml;hest v&auml;rskuse ja turdumuse v&auml;henemist, </eesti>
<inglise> -for products graded in classes other than the 'Extra' class, slight deterioration due to their development and their tendency to perish. </inglise>
<eesti> - muude toodete puhul, v.a ekstraklassi tooted, nende bioloogilisest arengust v&otilde;i riknemisohust p&otilde;hjustatud kvaliteedi v&auml;hest halvenemist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 1730/87 is hereby repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 1730/87 tunnistatakse kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. M&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse selle j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from the first day of the month following its entry into force. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. Br&uuml;ssel, 22. detsember 1999 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
